 hoping the pressure of presidential politics would force adifferent outcome.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Occupational Safety and HealthAdministration slapped a record $4.33 million fine on John Morrellandamp; Co., saying the meatpacker forced hundreds of injured employeesto work even immediately after surgery.   The fine, leveled Friday, reflected what Assistant LaborSecretary John A. Pendergrass called ``an employer who knew about aserious health hazard, saw the tragic toll on its workers and choseto ignore it.'' Morrell said it would fight the fine in court.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The American Telephone andamp; Telegraph Co. won aspirited competition to provide thousands of new computers to theDefense Department, establishing its position in the industry foryears to come with what has been described as the computer contractof the century.   The contract awarded Friday was worth $929.1 million, and ATandamp;Tofficials said it could ultimately exceed $1 billion depending onoptions excercised.</TEXT><NOTE>MORE</NOTE></DOC>